{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Tzqyo1nbz8DUa4CRtCL7Me","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue. The cluster status shows only 2 nodes (rabbitmq-0 and rabbitmq-1) are in the cluster. `rabbitmq-2` is running as a pod but not a member of the cluster.\n\nThe key clue is in the secret `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod`:\n- `rabbitmq-0`: `c3VwZXJzZWNyZXRjb29raWU=` → `supersecretcookie`\n- `rabbitmq-1`: `c3VwZXJzZWNyZXRjb29raWU=` → `supersecretcookie`\n- `rabbitmq-2`: `ZHJpZnRlZGNvb2tpZQ==` → `driftedcookie`\n\nThat's the problem—`rabbitmq-2` has a different Erlang cookie than the other nodes, so it can't authenticate and join the cluster. I need to update the secret to give `rabbitmq-2` the matching cookie, restart the pod to apply it, and then have it rejoin the cluster. Let me check how the cookie gets mounted into the pod to understand the mechanism.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1899,"cache_read_input_tokens":31321,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1899},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94b044ff-9d2e-4c57-b0cf-fa7da1af1ec0","uuid":"747f1305-16f9-4c5b-adc2-bd16d140122d","request_id":"req_011CcPxq9wJgtPZjap8VK5EV"}
