{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LRrD8gBSxmGith8krrng2N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The root cause is confirmed:\n- `rabbitmq-0` and `rabbitmq-1` have cookie `supersecretcookie`\n- `rabbitmq-2` has cookie `driftedcookie`\n\nThe init container copies the cookie from the secret `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` to an emptyDir volume that's mounted at `/var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie`. The main container mounts this emptyDir as read-only.\n\nThe fix is:\n1. Patch the secret to change `rabbitmq-2`'s cookie to `supersecretcookie` (base64 encoded: `c3VwZXJzZWNyZXRjb29raWU=`)\n2. Delete the `rabbitmq-2` pod to trigger a restart, which will run the init container again with the corrected cookie\n3. Once `rabbitmq-2` comes back up with the matching cookie, it should be able to rejoin the cluster using `rabbitmqctl join_cluster`\n\nI'm verifying the base64 encodings for both cookies to make sure the patch is correct.\n\nThe real complication here is that `rabbitmq-2`'s Mnesia database likely still has stale state from when it was using the wrong cookie. So after fixing the cookie and restarting, I'll need to reset the Mnesia data and have it resync from the cluster by stopping the app, resetting, joining the cluster explicitly, then starting the app again. about the data loss aspect. Since nodes 0 and 1 are healthy cluster members, the data is safe there. Node 2 likely has its own isolated Mnesia database since it never properly joined with the wrong cookie, so resetting it won't cause data loss—it'll just sync from the other nodes when it rejoins. My plan is to patch the secret with the correct cookie, delete the pod to force recreation, then manually reset and rejoin rabbitmq-2 if it doesn't auto-join by running the stop_app and reset commands.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3281,"cache_read_input_tokens":33220,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3281},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94b044ff-9d2e-4c57-b0cf-fa7da1af1ec0","uuid":"29d011e1-2ba7-435b-afbe-96710a527af4","request_id":"req_011CcPxqyAgXxVkgqR24frKk"}
