{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BPURRt9T34oB7Uxf26rfT1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`rabbitmq-2` still hasn't joined the cluster. Its Mnesia database probably has a different cluster view (from when it was running with the wrong cookie or standalone). I need to exec into `rabbitmq-2` and manually reset and rejoin it.\n\nThe steps are:\n1. `rabbitmqctl stop_app` - stops the RabbitMQ application (not the Erlang node)\n2. `rabbitmqctl reset` - wipes the Mnesia database on this node, forgetting its cluster membership\n3. `rabbitmqctl join_cluster rabbit@rabbitmq-0` - joins the existing cluster\n4. `rabbitmqctl start_app` - brings the application back online\n\nThis is safe because `rabbitmq-2` was never actually part of the cluster (it had the wrong cookie), so it has no unique data to lose. Once it rejoins and starts up, it'll sync state from the other nodes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":596,"cache_read_input_tokens":38717,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":596},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94b044ff-9d2e-4c57-b0cf-fa7da1af1ec0","uuid":"3ed77336-bbef-4844-8681-40e5f0c5f6d6","request_id":"req_011CcPxvrvmup9bhvEcJK1UR"}
